Germany Cuts Endowment Policy Interest Rate to 1.75%, FTD Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-02-22T18:57:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/germany-cuts-endowment-policy-interest-rate-to-1-75-ftd-says.html
  Germany ’s finance ministry decided
to reduce the guaranteed interest rate for new cash-value life
insurance policies by half a percentage point to 1.75 percent,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, without citing anyone.  The change won’t affect existing policies and will go into
effect for contracts signed from Jan. 1, 2012, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  